ght belief of the Self; or if he attains the grace of the Gnani Purush’.\n\n- Dada\n|\nThings is very primitive in the jungle - no place to shit, sleep on the ground like an animal, eat out of cans, no place to take a bath or nothing, clothes is all rotting off.\n\n- Winston Groom, Forrest Gump\n|\nPlaying it safe might not have hurt anyone, but it wouldn’t have inspired many, either.\n\n- Alex Staniforth, Icefall: The True Story of a Teenager on a Mission to the Top of the World\n|\nWhen perplexed, God appears to you in the form of wisdom; when troubled, in the form of peace; when sad, in the form of joy; when heartbroken, in the form of love.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nDream your dream; and realize that you are more than just the dreamer, you are the point of origin for its reality.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Unapologetically You: Reflections on Life and the Human Experience\n|\nYou know, sometimes I wish they would do this for us when we come home alive.\n\n- Jim\n|\nTo be productive, effective and to live a life of understanding and wisdom is not to waste time\n\n- Sunday\n|\nWhen a leader has an attitude of gratitude, it can create great differences in the lives of others.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWhat's it like?''Death? It's like being on holiday with a group of Germans.\n\n- Rob\n|\nTime is on its eternal journey at the same time it is motionless, emotionless and standing still.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWomen have become trained to be lone soldiers online, knowing that to send up a signal flare for help is more likely to attract enemies than allies.\n\n- Violet Blue, The Smart Girl's Guide to Privacy\n|\nDo little pink fairies sing and dance in your world, Peabody?''Sometimes, when it's very quiet and no one else can see.\n\n- J.D. Robb, Promises in Death\n|\nHe sits, strong and blunt as a Celtic cross, Clearly used to silence and an armchair: Tonight the wife and children will be quiet At slammed door and smoker's cough in the hall.\n\n- Seamus\n|\nTo love or have loved, that is enough.